{
  "texts": [
    "The goal of GAN is to place the generator and discriminator into equilibrium.",
    "However, there are downsides to using a GAN in its plain version:• Images are generated off some arbitrary noise.When generating a picture with specific features, you cannot determine what initial noise values would produce that picture but search over the entire distribution.",
    "• A GAN only distinguishes between ''real'' and ''fake'' images.",
    "But there are no constraints that a picture of a cat has to look like a cat.",
    "Thus, it might result in no actual object in a generated image, but the style looks like the picture."
  ]
}